description: Ukrainian and Western leaders welcomed a desperately needed aid package passed by the U.S. House of Representatives, as the Kremlin claimed the passage of the bill would “further ruin” Ukraine and cause more deaths.
title: Ukrainian and Western leaders laud U.S. aid package while the Kremlin warns of ‘further ruin’

description: With less than 100 days to go before the Paris 2024 Olympic games in France, concerns about pollution in Paris' Seine river are being raised.
title: Inside the Olympic effort to clean up the River Seine — and why it may be spoiled by a rainy day

description: The world’s top anti-doping regulator says 23 Chinese swimmers were cleared to compete at the Tokyo Olympics despite testing positive for a banned heart medication because it agreed with Chinese authorities and ruled that their samples had been contaminated.
title: Chinese swimmers won Olympic medals despite failed doping tests

description: Thousands of fans lined up along Pennsylvania Avenue on Saturday for the thrill of watching a Formula 1 race-winner blast down the iconic street in a championship-winning car.
title: Red Bull Formula 1 team turns Washington's iconic Pennsylvania Ave into a race track

description: Muslim American activists and organizers feel betrayed by President Joe Biden's support for additional aid to Israel, which is expected to become law next week.
title: Muslim Americans who soured on Biden see Israel aid package as further betrayal

description: Two Japanese navy helicopters carrying eight crewmembers were believed to have crashed in the Pacific Ocean south of Tokyo during a night-time training exercise, and rescuers were searching for the missing, Japan’s defense minister said.
title: 2 Japanese navy helicopters carrying 8 crew believed crashed in Pacific
